claim: Brooks Koepka failed to play at an American research university.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Roger L. Geiger , a historian specializing in the history of higher education in the United States , has argued that `` the model for the American research university was established by five colonial colleges chartered before the American Revolution  (  Harvard , Yale , Pennsylvania , Princeton , and Columbia  )  ; five state universities  (  Michigan , Wisconsin , Minnesota , Illinois , and California  )  ; and five private institutions conceived from their inception as research universities  (  MIT , Cornell , Johns Hopkins , Stanford , and Chicago  )  . ''
